---
---

<section id="practical-info" class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white scroll-mt-20">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <p class="font-display italic text-gold text-lg mb-2">Good to know</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-wine tracking-tight">Practical Info</h2>
      <div class="section-rule mt-5" aria-hidden="true"><span>§</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

      <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-wine mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-xl">🌡️</span> Weather
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70">
          July in Burgundy is warm and sunny: expect <strong>25&ndash;30&deg;C</strong> during the
          day, cooling to 15&ndash;18&deg;C at night. Occasional afternoon thunderstorms are possible,
          but generally it&rsquo;s beautiful summer weather.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-wine mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-xl">🧳</span> What to Pack
        </h3>
        <ul class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 space-y-1">
          <li>&#8226; Light summer clothing + one warm layer for evenings</li>
          <li>&#8226; Swimwear &amp; towel (pool towels may be limited)</li>
          <li>&#8226; Comfortable shoes for walking/cycling</li>
          <li>&#8226; Something dressy for the anniversary party</li>
          <li>&#8226; Red, white &amp; blue outfit for July 4th!</li>
          <li>&#8226; Sunscreen, hat, and sunglasses</li>
          <li>&#8226; Bug spray (countryside evenings!)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-wine mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-xl">🔌</span> Power &amp; Wi-Fi
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 mb-2">
          France uses <strong>Type E</strong> power plugs (230V, 50Hz). If you&rsquo;re coming
          from the UK, US, or elsewhere, bring an adapter.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70">
          The venue has <strong>Wi-Fi</strong> throughout. We&rsquo;ll share the password on arrival.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-wine mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-xl">🏥</span> Health &amp; Safety
        </h3>
        <ul class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 space-y-1">
          <li>&#8226; <strong>Hospital:</strong> Centre Hospitalier d&rsquo;Autun (~20 min drive)</li>
          <li>&#8226; <strong>Pharmacy:</strong> Pharmacie d&rsquo;Epinac, Place de la R&eacute;publique</li>
          <li>&#8226; <strong>Emergency:</strong> Dial <strong>112</strong> (EU) or <strong>15</strong> (SAMU)</li>
          <li>&#8226; EU citizens: bring your EHIC/GHIC card</li>
          <li>&#8226; Non-EU: travel insurance strongly recommended</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-wine mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-xl">🛒</span> Shopping &amp; Essentials
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 mb-2">
          There&rsquo;s a small supermarket in Epinac for basics. For a larger shop,
          head to <strong>Autun</strong> (20 min) which has several supermarkets (Carrefour, Lidl).
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70">
          The local <strong>Boulangerie Royer David</strong> in Epinac opens at 6am for fresh bread
          and pastries (closed Mondays).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-wine mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-xl">💶</span> Money &amp; Language
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 mb-2">
          Currency is <strong>Euro (&euro;)</strong>. Cards are accepted most places, but
          bring some cash for small vendors and markets.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70">
          French is the local language. English is spoken at tourist sites and restaurants,
          but a few French phrases go a long way!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-wine mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-xl">🛂</span> Visas &amp; Entry
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70">
          France is in the Schengen Area. EU/EEA citizens need only an ID card. US, UK,
          Canadian, and Australian citizens can enter visa-free for up to 90 days.
          Check your country&rsquo;s requirements &mdash; if you need an invitation letter,
          let us know!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-wine mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-xl">👶</span> Kids at the Venue
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70">
          The venue has a heated pool (please supervise children at all times),
          a game room with games and TV, and large outdoor grounds. We&rsquo;ll have
          babysitters arranged for the anniversary party evening. Bring pool floaties
          for little ones!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-wine mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-xl">💬</span> Stay Connected
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70">
          We&rsquo;ll set up a <strong>WhatsApp group</strong> for real-time coordination
          during the week &mdash; ride sharing, dinner plans, activity sign-ups, and
          general fun. Link will be shared before the trip.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
